## Getting Started 

  

This tutorial assumes you have Anaconda installed on your system. If not, follow the instructions in the next section to install Anaconda. 

  

## Installing Anaconda 

  

Anaconda is a distribution of Python and R programming languages for scientific computing, that aims to simplify package management and deployment. You can download and install Anaconda from the [official website](https://www.anaconda.com/products/distribution). 

  

Follow the installation instructions for your operating system. 

  

## Installing Pandas 

  

Once Anaconda is installed, you can easily install Pandas using the following command in your terminal or Anaconda prompt: 

  

```bash 

conda install pandas 

 